member.name: T:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.NotificationMode
member.summary: Specifies how often Stat Server will send updates on the requested statistical values.

member.name: F:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.NotificationMode.Immediate
member.summary: Stat Server reports statistics whenever a statistical value changes; for time-related statistics, Immediate means that Stat Server will report the current value whenever a statistical value changes, but it will also report that value periodically, using the specified notification frequency.

member.name: F:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.NotificationMode.Periodical
member.summary: Stat Server reports statistics based on the time period you request.

member.name: F:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.NotificationMode.NoNotification
member.summary: Allows you to retrieve statistics when you want them.

member.name: F:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.NotificationMode.Reset
member.summary: Stat Server reports the current value right before setting the statistical value to zero (0).

member.name: T:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.StatisticCategory
member.summary: A statistical category is a general definition, for example, "TotalNumberPerSecond" or "CurrentTargetState," that determines how to calculate a statistic on the basis of one or two lists of actions (masks) supplied as separate elements of a statistical type.

member.name: T:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.StatisticProfile
member.summary: Determines which type of statistics configuration information is being requested by a RequestGetStatisticProfile.

member.name: T:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.StatisticInterval
member.summary: This enum defines time intervals used for calculating historical, aggregate values for statistics.

member.name: F:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.StatisticInterval.GrowingWindow
member.summary: Resets statistics to zero at one or more specified times: for example, at midnight and then every three hours after that.

member.name: F:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.StatisticInterval.SinceLogin
member.summary: Aggregates statistical data only for Agent-based statistics: the statistics are set to zero (0) at the moment of agent login and continue to accumulate so long as an agent is associated with a specific place.

member.name: F:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.StatisticInterval.SlidingWindow
member.summary: Tracks the last several seconds of activity, using a number of seconds that you specify, with an option to specify how often to sample the statistic (which defaults to every 10 seconds); for example, the last 600 seconds, sampled every 2 seconds.

member.name: F:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.StatisticInterval.SlidingSelection
member.summary: Tracks the last several occurrences of an activity, using a number of activities that you specify, for example, the last 5 calls.

member.name: T:Genesyslab.Platform.Reporting.Protocols.StatServer.StatisticSubject
